data.title: Aselin Debison - Age, Family, Bio
data.meta_description: Aselin Debison: her birthday, what she did before fame, her family life, fun trivia facts, popularity rankings, and more.
data.text:
About

Singer who rose to fame as a child when she released her debut album, The Littlest Angel, a Christmas album released in 2001. She has since released a number of popular albums, including Sweet is the Melody, which features covers of songs by artists like Garth Brooks and Mike Oldfield.

Before Fame

Her musical career began at the age of nine after she sang at a mining rally in her hometown of Glace Bay, Nova Scotia.

Trivia

She enrolled at St. Francis Xavier University to study human kinetics.

Family Life

In 2012, she married former singer Sebastian Tonik.
